Unfortunately, I couldn't give this restaurant a 0 out of 5 stars. Door dash is to blame aswell for this review. If either party are not going to respond to me, then my honest opinion and review are going to hurt where it matters. I hope people take the time to read this and not order from these guys ever again. Only through our bad and unfortunate experience, should  they hopefully change their treatment of customers. Pandemic or not, you should never be un-professional to people.  Now straight to what happened. It all started when I ordered food from this place using Door dash. The food came in later than the expected delivery time. When it finally did, the food was cold, didn't taste good at all, and in addition, I was missing two fully paid items.  So, like a concern paying customer, I went ahead and called up the restaurant. Some guy worker picked up. I went ahead to explain the problem. For FIVE whole minutes he argues with me and tells me that the missing items weren't missing.  This made me feel a certain way, like a liar and a lesser man. "Like I paid for these two items and they weren't in the bag", as I kept explaining to him.  After the FIVE minutes, he then tells me sorry and that he was going to send me my items asap. An hour pass, nothing, two hour, nothing. At that very moment I was fed up( This was last night BTW)(April 30th, 2020).  I then try to reach Door dash and couldn't get a hold with them, like at all. I had better customer service using Grub hub in the past, for they would actually call the restaurant up and do something about it. Door dash is a poor excuse for a food service app. I wouldn't recommend this app to anyone.  Thanks for reading, be safe and don't ever order from these guys ever again. God bless!
